---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaBand from '../components/CtaBand.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Our Consent-First Promise | Spry"
  description="Exactly how we run safe scam drills: personal consent, gentle coaching, no shame, no bank access, and channels that earn their way in."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="kicker">Our promise</p>
      <h1>How we run drills on someone we've never met — carefully.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Sending a practice scam to someone's mother is a serious thing to do. Here is exactly how
        we handle that responsibility.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section--tight section" style="padding-bottom: 96px;">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <div class="promise-item">
        <h2>1. Consent, personally and always.</h2>
        <p>
          No senior is ever enrolled without their own knowing agreement (or their legally
          designated decision-maker's, where appropriate). They know drills will come; they just
          don't know when — that's what makes practice honest. Enrollment can be withdrawn any
          time, instantly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="promise-item">
        <h2>2. Gentle by design.</h2>
        <p>
          Drills never involve real money, real risk, or real consequences. Coaching moments are
          brief, warm, and private. No scores are shared beyond the family members your parent
          approved. We never use fear, shame, or “gotcha” language — the research is clear that it
          backfires, and it's also just not who we are.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="promise-item">
        <h2>3. Right-fit enrollment.</h2>
        <p>
          Spry is designed for cognitively healthy adults who manage their own email and
          phone. It is not appropriate for people with significant cognitive impairment, and our
          enrollment process screens for fit. If a Resilience Report trend suggests changing needs, we
          tell the family privately and help them decide what's next.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="promise-item">
        <h2>4. Channels earn their way in.</h2>
        <p>
          We start with email. Text and voice drills are added only with prior express
          <strong>written</strong> consent, per federal telemarketing law (TCPA) — a bar we treat
          as a floor, not a ceiling.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="promise-item">
        <h2>5. Data minimalism.</h2>
        <p>
          We collect only what drills require (name, contact channels, drill history). We never
          access bank accounts, credit reports, or financial data. We never sell personal data.
          Ever.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="promise-item">
        <h2>6. Debrief, always.</h2>
        <p>
          Every missed drill ends in the same place: a clear “this was a safe practice from
          Spry” message and a specific, usable lesson. Nobody is ever left wondering whether
          it was real.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top: 40px;">
        If you're evaluating us — as a family, a community, or a regulator — and want to go deeper
        on any of this, write us:
        <a href="mailto:hello@sprysafe.com">hello@sprysafe.com</a>. We'll
        answer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand />
</Base>

<style>
  .promise-item {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--amber);
    padding-left: 26px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .promise-item h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
  .promise-item p { color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 0; }
</style>
